Let me analyze the target structure and provide step-by-step instructions using the available blocks.

Analysis of the Main Target Image:
The structure consists of two distinct buildings side by side:
1. Left Building: A small house-like structure with:
   - Two green vertical pillars as base
   - A yellow horizontal beam
   - A red arch structure
   - An orange triangular roof

2. Right Building: A larger complex structure with:
   - Two green vertical pillars at the ends
   - Red arch base with two arches
   - Two yellow semicylindrical blocks on top
   - Three yellow vertical towers
   - One green vertical block between yellow towers

Assembly Instructions:
{
    Step1: Move block with index 4 (left green pillar of left building)
    Step2: Move block with index 4 (right green pillar of left building)
    Step3: Move block with index 7 (yellow horizontal beam for left building)
    Step4: Move block with index 1 (red arch for left building)
    Step5: Move block with index 15 (orange triangular roof piece)
    Step6: Move block with index 4 (rightmost green pillar of right building)
    Step7: Move block with index 4 (second green pillar from right)
    Step8: Move block with index 1 (right red arch)
    Step9: Move block with index 1 (left red arch)
    Step10: Move block with index 11 (right yellow semicylinder)
    Step11: Move block with index 11 (left yellow semicylinder)
    Step12: Move block with index 8 (rightmost yellow tower)
    Step13: Move block with index 3 (middle green block)
    Step14: Move block with index 8 (leftmost yellow tower)
}
